.SS generate
.PP
.I Generate a signing keypair + cert
.PP
.B Category:
Keys
.br
.B Maturity:
experimental
.PP
.B SYNTAX
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
lamboot\-signing\-keys generate [\-\-type db|kek|pk] [\-\-size N] [\-\-cn NAME] [\-\-days N] [\-\-output PREFIX]
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B ARGUMENTS
.PP
.RS 4
.TP
.B \-\-type db
\-\-type db
.TP
.B kek
kek
.TP
.B pk
Key role (default: db)
.TP
.B \-\-size N
RSA key size (default: 2048 for db, 4096 for pk/kek)
.TP
.B \-\-cn NAME
Subject CommonName
.TP
.B \-\-days N
Validity (default: 1095 for db, 3650 for pk/kek)
.TP
.B \-\-output PREFIX
Output prefix; produces PREFIX.key + PREFIX.crt + PREFIX.der (default: ./<type>)
.TP
.B \-\-force\-4096
Override RSA\-2048 constraint for db (dangerous; shim freezes per Debian #1013320)
.RE
.PP
.B EXAMPLES
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
lamboot\-signing\-keys generate \-\-type db \-\-cn \'My db Key 2026\'
lamboot\-signing\-keys generate \-\-type pk \-\-output /tmp/mypk
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B NOTES
.PP
.RS 4
RSA\-2048 is enforced for db keys because Debian bug #1013320 causes shim to freeze verifying RSA\-4096 MOK certs. RSA\-4096 is safe for PK/KEK. Private key is 0600; cert is 0644.
.RE
.PP
.B OFFLINE:
No \- requires online system
.br
.B PRIVILEGE:
Runs unprivileged
.PP
.B SEE ALSO
.PP
.RS 4
inspect, mok\-enroll, status
.RE
.PP
.B DOCUMENTATION URL
.PP
.RS 4
.UR https://lamboot.dev/tools/signing-keys/generate
.UE
.RE
