.SS rotate
.PP
.I Rotate a db/kek/pk keypair, cross\-signing with the parent key
.PP
.B Category:
Keys
.br
.B Maturity:
experimental
.PP
.B SYNTAX
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
lamboot\-signing\-keys rotate TYPE \-\-old\-key K \-\-old\-cert C [\-\-new\-cn NAME] [\-\-parent\-key K \-\-parent\-cert C] [\-\-output\-dir DIR]
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B ARGUMENTS
.PP
.RS 4
.TP
.B TYPE
db 
.TP
.B  kek 
 kek 
.TP
.B  pk
 pk
.TP
.B \-\-old\-key PATH
Existing private key being rotated
.TP
.B \-\-old\-cert PATH
Existing cert being rotated
.TP
.B \-\-new\-cn NAME
CN for the new cert (default: inherits old CN with \'\-rotated\-YYYYMMDD\' suffix)
.TP
.B \-\-parent\-key PATH
Parent private key for cross\-sign (KEK for db rotation, PK for KEK rotation). Optional; if absent, rotation produces a self\-signed new cert and emits a warning.
.TP
.B \-\-parent\-cert PATH
Parent cert for cross\-sign (must match \-\-parent\-key)
.TP
.B \-\-output\-dir DIR
Rotation artifacts directory (default: ./rotation\-TYPE\-YYYYMMDD\-HHMMSS)
.RE
.PP
.B EXAMPLES
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
sudo lamboot\-signing\-keys rotate db \-\-old\-key keys/db.key \-\-old\-cert keys/db.crt \-\-parent\-key keys/kek.key \-\-parent\-cert keys/kek.crt
sudo lamboot\-signing\-keys rotate kek \-\-old\-key keys/kek.key \-\-old\-cert keys/kek.crt \-\-parent\-key keys/pk.key \-\-parent\-cert keys/pk.crt
sudo lamboot\-signing\-keys rotate pk \-\-old\-key keys/pk.key \-\-old\-cert keys/pk.crt
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B NOTES
.PP
.RS 4
Generates a new keypair with the same RSA size + validity defaults as generate, then cross\-signs the new cert with the parent key (db←KEK, KEK←PK, PK←self). Produces a timestamped rotation directory containing old + new keypairs, a transition manifest, and re\-enrollment instructions. Both old and new keys remain valid during the transition window; stragglers can be re\-signed with either old or new db until distribution completes. See KEY\-GENERATION.md §6.1.
.RE
.PP
.B OFFLINE:
No \- requires online system
.br
.B PRIVILEGE:
Runs unprivileged
.PP
.B SEE ALSO
.PP
.RS 4
generate, generate\-hierarchy, mok\-enroll
.RE
.PP
.B DOCUMENTATION URL
.PP
.RS 4
.UR https://lamboot.dev/tools/signing-keys/rotate
.UE
