.RE
.PP
.SS sign\-binary
.PP
.I Sign a binary (Scope 1)
.PP
.B Category:
Release Eng
.br
.B Maturity:
experimental
.PP
.B SYNTAX
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
lamboot\-signing\-keys sign\-binary BINARY \-\-key KEY \-\-cert CERT [\-\-output OUT] [\-\-sbat CSV|\-\-sbat\-file PATH|\-\-no\-sbat]
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B ARGUMENTS
.PP
.RS 4
.TP
.B BINARY
File to sign
.TP
.B \-\-key PATH
Private key
.TP
.B \-\-cert PATH
Cert
.TP
.B \-\-sbat CSV
Inline SBAT CSV line (e.g. "lamboot,1,LamCo,lamboot,0.8.4,https://lamboot.dev/sbat")
.TP
.B \-\-sbat\-file PATH
Path to SBAT CSV file (header row + one entry per component); overrides \-\-sbat
.TP
.B \-\-no\-sbat
Skip SBAT section injection (NOT recommended — shim may refuse to chain unsigned SBAT binaries)
.RE
.PP
.B EXAMPLES
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
lamboot\-signing\-keys sign\-binary dist/lambootx64.efi \-\-key keys/db.key \-\-cert keys/db.crt
lamboot\-signing\-keys sign\-binary dist/lambootx64.efi \-\-key keys/db.key \-\-cert keys/db.crt \-\-sbat\-file /etc/lamboot/sbat.csv
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B NOTES
.PP
.RS 4
Injects a .sbat PE section before sbsign if not present. Resolution order: \-\-sbat\-file > \-\-sbat > /etc/lamboot/sbat.csv > built\-in default. Uses objcopy \-\-add\-section .sbat=PATH with appropriate flags. SBAT format per https://github.com/rhboot/shim/blob/main/SBAT.md. Pass \-\-no\-sbat to skip injection entirely (e.g. when binary already has .sbat).
.RE
.PP
.B OFFLINE:
No \- requires online system
.br
.B PRIVILEGE:
Runs unprivileged
.PP
.B SEE ALSO
.PP
.RS 4
generate\-hierarchy, lamboot\-uki\-build
.RE
.PP
.B DOCUMENTATION URL
.PP
.RS 4
.UR https://lamboot.dev/tools/signing-keys/sign-binary
.UE
